1
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:32,000
=Our Days=

2
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,720
(Adapted from Lang Lang's original novel
"The Prime of the Goddess")

3
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:38,160
=Episode 5=

4
00:01:45,375 --> 00:01:46,996
Good morning, boss.

5
00:01:48,616 --> 00:01:50,036
You've met Jiang Hongbin.

6
00:01:52,295 --> 00:01:53,396
How was it?

7
00:01:56,096 --> 00:01:57,196
Why do you care?

8
00:01:58,015 --> 00:01:59,476
I'm just curious.

9
00:02:00,495 --> 00:02:03,356
How should I put it? Nothing unusual.

10
00:02:05,015 --> 00:02:07,196
He even thought of asking us

11
00:02:07,295 --> 00:02:08,556
what we like to eat

12
00:02:08,655 --> 00:02:10,715
and remember my Dad's favorite drink.

13
00:02:11,096 --> 00:02:12,836
I'd say he's attentive.

14
00:02:15,736 --> 00:02:18,075
It's good that he's attentive.

15
00:02:18,416 --> 00:02:19,596
Not really.

16
00:02:19,655 --> 00:02:21,415
I still feel insecure.

17
00:02:21,416 --> 00:02:23,094
We were supposed to dine
at my house that day.

18
00:02:23,095 --> 00:02:27,075
But he changed his mind
because it was already too late.

19
00:02:27,136 --> 00:02:30,515
We finally ended up dining
at a restaurant instead.

20
00:02:33,056 --> 00:02:34,395
Have a look.

21
00:02:35,736 --> 00:02:36,795
What is it?

22
00:02:38,255 --> 00:02:41,075
This woman's name is Ming Wei.

23
00:02:42,176 --> 00:02:43,895
She's been by his side for many years.

24
00:02:43,896 --> 00:02:46,756
Last Saturday, someone even saw them
having supper together.

25
00:02:48,016 --> 00:02:49,636
I feel like,

26
00:02:50,616 --> 00:02:53,196
no matter how many stories
he tries to cook up,

27
00:02:53,775 --> 00:02:55,055
the fact that Xiang Nan

28
00:02:55,056 --> 00:02:56,636
is willing to marry him

29
00:02:57,215 --> 00:02:59,316
is undeniably a great achievement.

30
00:03:01,176 --> 00:03:02,476
Whose achievement?

31
00:03:02,935 --> 00:03:04,415
Do we have to thank the heavens

32
00:03:04,416 --> 00:03:06,156
for letting him marry Xiang Nan?

33
00:03:07,935 --> 00:03:10,036
That depends on what you expect.

34
00:03:10,336 --> 00:03:11,476
I have to go.

35
00:03:12,456 --> 00:03:13,795
Thank you.

36
00:03:23,935 --> 00:03:24,995
Xiang Nan.

37
00:03:25,215 --> 00:03:25,895
Where are you?

38
00:03:25,896 --> 00:03:26,916
What are you doing?

39
00:03:27,136 --> 00:03:28,335
I'm in Shanghai now.

40
00:03:28,336 --> 00:03:29,275
Is there anything?

41
00:03:29,616 --> 00:03:30,995
You're in Shanghai?

42
00:03:31,056 --> 00:03:32,395
What are you doing there?

43
00:03:41,095 --> 00:03:42,395
Hi, Sis.

44
00:03:44,815 --> 00:03:46,494
Why would you suddenly arrange

45
00:03:46,495 --> 00:03:48,356
for a premarital medical test?

46
00:03:48,775 --> 00:03:50,115
Jiang did.

47
00:03:50,136 --> 00:03:50,855
He told me

48
00:03:50,856 --> 00:03:52,455
he's arranged for a
premarital medical test

49
00:03:52,456 --> 00:03:53,615
and wants me to get checked

50
00:03:53,616 --> 00:03:54,955
thoroughly.

51
00:03:55,456 --> 00:03:57,455
Take a look at the never-ending list

52
00:03:57,456 --> 00:03:59,316
of items to be checked.

53
00:03:59,616 --> 00:04:00,374
Besides,

54
00:04:00,375 --> 00:04:01,675
the ones back here

55
00:04:01,856 --> 00:04:05,196
are genetically-related tests.

56
00:04:05,375 --> 00:04:07,036
Have you arranged for one?

57
00:04:07,296 --> 00:04:08,356
No.

58
00:04:09,375 --> 00:04:10,675
Let me ask them

59
00:04:10,695 --> 00:04:12,415
how long does it take
to complete these tests.

60
00:04:12,416 --> 00:04:13,955
Don't worry about it first.

61
00:04:15,375 --> 00:04:16,876
We have just

62
00:04:16,975 --> 00:04:18,596
met Jiang Hongbin once

63
00:04:18,815 --> 00:04:20,476
over a meal.

64
00:04:21,255 --> 00:04:24,156
Xiang Nan, don't you think
that this relationship is too rushed?

65
00:04:24,656 --> 00:04:25,934
It's only been 6 months.

66
00:04:25,935 --> 00:04:27,995
Even if you've been together
for one, two,

67
00:04:28,296 --> 00:04:29,975
or even five years,

68
00:04:29,976 --> 00:04:32,276
it won't be enough
to fully understand a person.

69
00:04:33,616 --> 00:04:35,036
Sis.

70
00:04:35,135 --> 00:04:37,315
Although it's only been 6 months,

71
00:04:37,375 --> 00:04:40,036
I am confident that I know him well.

72
00:04:40,135 --> 00:04:41,875
He tells me everything.

73
00:04:42,495 --> 00:04:44,555
All I have to do is believe in him.

74
00:04:44,976 --> 00:04:46,596
Isn't that enough?

75
00:04:52,296 --> 00:04:53,615
Do you have something else

76
00:04:53,616 --> 00:04:54,836
you want to tell me?

77
00:04:56,575 --> 00:04:57,374
No.

78
00:04:57,375 --> 00:04:58,454
If that's the case,

79
00:04:58,455 --> 00:04:59,795
why the grim face?

80
00:05:01,895 --> 00:05:02,875
Xiang Nan.

81
00:05:05,056 --> 00:05:05,916
Jiang.

82
00:05:05,935 --> 00:05:06,995
Sis.

83
00:05:07,296 --> 00:05:08,435
What brings you here?

84
00:05:08,495 --> 00:05:09,975
I happen to call Xiang Nan just now

85
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:11,254
and she told me she's in Shanghai.

86
00:05:11,255 --> 00:05:12,235
So I came.

87
00:05:12,335 --> 00:05:13,334
Jiang.

88
00:05:13,335 --> 00:05:15,356
I've read through the handbook.

89
00:05:15,495 --> 00:05:16,775
Why are there so many tests?

90
00:05:16,776 --> 00:05:17,415
Even my genes

91
00:05:17,416 --> 00:05:18,615
have to be tested.

92
00:05:18,616 --> 00:05:19,494
Don't you think

93
00:05:19,495 --> 00:05:21,276
it's too comprehensive and exhaustive?

94
00:05:22,015 --> 00:05:22,975
Look at me,

95
00:05:22,976 --> 00:05:24,175
I have two handbooks.

96
00:05:24,176 --> 00:05:25,995
I have a lot more tests than you.

97
00:05:26,695 --> 00:05:28,235
Drop the act, Jiang.

98
00:05:28,335 --> 00:05:30,055
Something's not right here.

99
00:05:30,056 --> 00:05:32,235
I just had a sudden realization.

100
00:05:32,296 --> 00:05:33,095
Do you suspect

101
00:05:33,096 --> 00:05:34,254
anything wrong

102
00:05:34,255 --> 00:05:35,795
with my family's genes?

103
00:05:36,015 --> 00:05:37,716
What are you talking about?

104
00:05:37,736 --> 00:05:39,334
All I wanted was for us

105
00:05:39,335 --> 00:05:40,716
to have a healthy baby

106
00:05:41,096 --> 00:05:42,574
after we get married.

107
00:05:42,575 --> 00:05:43,855
What's wrong with that?

108
00:05:43,856 --> 00:05:44,855
I don't want to

109
00:05:44,856 --> 00:05:46,014
have a baby so soon.

110
00:05:46,015 --> 00:05:47,235
Xiang Nan.

111
00:05:47,255 --> 00:05:49,454
I surely will have
more health problems than you.

112
00:05:49,455 --> 00:05:52,716
Don't give me the cold shoulder
after my report is out.

113
00:05:52,895 --> 00:05:54,494
I can't guarantee that.

114
00:05:54,495 --> 00:05:56,995
It depends
on the specific problems you have.

115
00:05:57,815 --> 00:05:59,276
How realistic you are.

116
00:05:59,695 --> 00:06:00,735
Mr. and Mrs. Jiang.

117
00:06:00,736 --> 00:06:02,014
We're ready to serve you.

118
00:06:02,015 --> 00:06:02,694
Please follow me.

119
00:06:02,695 --> 00:06:03,555
- Okay.
- Okay.

120
00:06:03,575 --> 00:06:04,334
Let's go.

121
00:06:04,335 --> 00:06:06,254
Xiang Nan. You go in first.

122
00:06:06,255 --> 00:06:07,476
Take your things.

123
00:06:07,776 --> 00:06:10,156
Let me speak to Mr. Jiang for a while.

124
00:06:10,255 --> 00:06:11,694
All right. I go in first.

125
00:06:11,695 --> 00:06:12,295
Okay.

126
00:06:12,296 --> 00:06:12,574
Go on.

127
00:06:12,575 --> 00:06:13,675
Bye, Sis.

128
00:06:15,656 --> 00:06:16,295
Mr. Jiang.

129
00:06:16,296 --> 00:06:17,276
Hold on.

130
00:06:17,375 --> 00:06:19,076
Just call me Hongbin.

131
00:06:19,375 --> 00:06:20,435
Sure.

132
00:06:21,296 --> 00:06:22,315
Hongbin.

133
00:06:29,416 --> 00:06:30,295
Sis...

134
00:06:30,296 --> 00:06:31,396
do you

135
00:06:31,495 --> 00:06:33,356
have something to say to me?

136
00:06:35,056 --> 00:06:35,916
I'll...

137
00:06:36,176 --> 00:06:37,574
just cut to the chase.

138
00:06:37,575 --> 00:06:38,516
Go ahead.

139
00:06:40,495 --> 00:06:43,036
Is it true that you have a girlfriend

140
00:06:43,416 --> 00:06:45,596
who's been with you for many years

141
00:06:48,895 --> 00:06:50,476
before you met Xiang Nan?

142
00:06:52,935 --> 00:06:54,795
Are you referring to Ming Wei?

143
00:06:54,976 --> 00:06:57,276
Right, I think that's her name.

144
00:06:59,296 --> 00:07:00,675
I'll be honest with you.

145
00:07:00,976 --> 00:07:03,095
Ming Wei is indeed my ex-girlfriend.

146
00:07:03,096 --> 00:07:05,635
Of course, she's also my business partner.

147
00:07:06,695 --> 00:07:08,875
Are you guys still working together?

148
00:07:09,935 --> 00:07:11,156
Sometimes.

149
00:07:11,335 --> 00:07:12,995
Is Xiang Nan aware of it?

150
00:07:13,656 --> 00:07:14,635
Yes.

151
00:07:15,976 --> 00:07:17,795
Does she mind?

152
00:07:23,616 --> 00:07:24,795
Are you worried

153
00:07:25,335 --> 00:07:27,755
that we might reach out
to each other constantly?

154
00:07:28,815 --> 00:07:29,596
Yes.

155
00:07:30,895 --> 00:07:31,956
Put it this way.

156
00:07:32,815 --> 00:07:34,276
Since I've decided

157
00:07:34,375 --> 00:07:35,716
to marry Xiang Nan,

158
00:07:35,776 --> 00:07:37,055
I'll make sure to

159
00:07:37,056 --> 00:07:39,115
sort out my past accordingly

160
00:07:39,216 --> 00:07:40,956
and be fully accountable to Xiang Nan.

161
00:07:41,335 --> 00:07:42,755
Don't you worry.

162
00:07:45,216 --> 00:07:46,555
Yes, right.

163
00:07:46,976 --> 00:07:48,655
You'll sort it out. Okay.

164
00:07:48,656 --> 00:07:50,215
I feel less worried now.

165
00:07:50,216 --> 00:07:52,076
Whatever happens between you two,

166
00:07:52,495 --> 00:07:54,574
just explain it to Xiang Nan will do.

167
00:07:54,575 --> 00:07:57,014
- Right.
- Xiang Nan is still very young.

168
00:07:57,015 --> 00:07:58,435
Since you're older than her,

169
00:07:58,575 --> 00:08:00,076
you should be more understanding.

170
00:08:00,536 --> 00:08:01,814
Clear the air before your marriage

171
00:08:01,815 --> 00:08:02,574
to avoid

172
00:08:02,575 --> 00:08:04,014
getting into a conflict later

173
00:08:04,015 --> 00:08:05,596
due to some hearsay.

174
00:08:05,616 --> 00:08:07,836
Especially my old man,

175
00:08:07,856 --> 00:08:09,315
he can't bear to hear such news

176
00:08:09,656 --> 00:08:12,396
or he will explode with anger.

177
00:08:12,935 --> 00:08:14,315
Thank you for your consideration.

178
00:08:14,375 --> 00:08:15,315
I totally get it.

179
00:08:15,335 --> 00:08:16,356
Don't worry.

180
00:08:16,455 --> 00:08:18,374
Well then, you may go.

181
00:08:18,375 --> 00:08:20,134
- Sure, I'll head in now. Have a sit.
- I will.

182
00:08:20,135 --> 00:08:20,535
Bye-bye.

183
00:08:20,536 --> 00:08:21,315
Okay.

184
00:08:45,136 --> 00:08:46,796
Did you just return home?

185
00:08:47,975 --> 00:08:50,155
It's been two weeks.

186
00:08:50,815 --> 00:08:51,574
Have you

187
00:08:51,575 --> 00:08:52,995
forgotten about me?

188
00:08:53,855 --> 00:08:55,055
Let me take a look.

189
00:08:55,056 --> 00:08:55,814
Does it hurt?

190
00:08:55,815 --> 00:08:56,655
No. It doesn't hurt.

191
00:08:56,656 --> 00:08:58,535
I told you everything
on the phone, I'm okay.

192
00:08:58,536 --> 00:09:00,155
You don't have to come all the way here.

193
00:09:00,215 --> 00:09:02,135
No use inspecting my wound,
you're not a doctor.

194
00:09:02,136 --> 00:09:03,115
So what did the doctor say?

195
00:09:03,176 --> 00:09:04,235
What did the doctor say?

196
00:09:04,256 --> 00:09:05,574
I'll put your things here.

197
00:09:05,575 --> 00:09:06,515
I have to go to work.

198
00:09:07,615 --> 00:09:08,515
Xiang Zhong.

199
00:09:08,896 --> 00:09:09,875
Can you go later?

200
00:09:10,016 --> 00:09:11,556
I have something to tell you both.

201
00:09:15,416 --> 00:09:16,334
Your great-aunt

202
00:09:16,335 --> 00:09:17,574
said she saw you at the hospital.

203
00:09:17,575 --> 00:09:19,135
That's how I know you got injured.

204
00:09:19,136 --> 00:09:20,155
Have some milk.

205
00:09:20,695 --> 00:09:21,535
Look at you,

206
00:09:21,536 --> 00:09:22,775
your bones are so brittle.

207
00:09:22,776 --> 00:09:23,836
You lack calcium.

208
00:09:24,455 --> 00:09:26,255
Why didn't you tell me

209
00:09:26,256 --> 00:09:27,915
when Haiyang got injured?

210
00:09:28,815 --> 00:09:29,934
There's no need to.

211
00:09:29,935 --> 00:09:31,094
I'm doing fine.

212
00:09:31,095 --> 00:09:32,135
Fine?

213
00:09:32,136 --> 00:09:33,655
What if you were blinded?

214
00:09:33,656 --> 00:09:35,155
What actually happened to you?

215
00:09:35,215 --> 00:09:36,814
Well,

216
00:09:36,815 --> 00:09:39,814
I just had too much to drink

217
00:09:39,815 --> 00:09:40,854
and got drunk.

218
00:09:40,855 --> 00:09:42,135
And then,

219
00:09:42,136 --> 00:09:43,734
I had an accident.

220
00:09:43,735 --> 00:09:44,734
Yeah, go on.

221
00:09:44,735 --> 00:09:46,635
Make up a better story, will you?

222
00:09:46,695 --> 00:09:47,535
Old habits die hard.

223
00:09:47,536 --> 00:09:49,076
So how much did you drink?

224
00:09:49,136 --> 00:09:52,895
Why didn't you look after him, Xiang Zhong?
You shouldn't let him drink too much.

225
00:09:52,896 --> 00:09:53,854
What if he gets into

226
00:09:53,855 --> 00:09:55,574
a more serious accident?

227
00:09:55,575 --> 00:09:57,495
I was the one who drank too much.

228
00:09:57,496 --> 00:10:00,094
Why are you blaming her?
She has nothing to do with it.

229
00:10:00,095 --> 00:10:01,556
You're always like this.

230
00:10:01,935 --> 00:10:03,275
Too protective of her.

231
00:10:03,455 --> 00:10:05,175
One day, if you were really

232
00:10:05,176 --> 00:10:06,956
blinded or injured your head,

233
00:10:07,256 --> 00:10:09,436
will she still remain by your side?

234
00:10:10,136 --> 00:10:11,076
No.

235
00:10:14,735 --> 00:10:16,115
Did you hear that?

236
00:10:17,056 --> 00:10:18,235
I want a divorce.

237
00:10:33,176 --> 00:10:34,356
Deng Haiyang.

238
00:10:35,335 --> 00:10:36,596
Have you cheated on her?

239
00:10:36,776 --> 00:10:37,836
No.

240
00:10:38,855 --> 00:10:40,436
Did he domestically abuse you?

241
00:10:40,615 --> 00:10:41,596
That's impossible.

242
00:10:41,656 --> 00:10:43,015
So you cheated on him?

243
00:10:43,016 --> 00:10:44,334
Mom, what are you saying?

244
00:10:44,335 --> 00:10:45,895
Please stop talking nonsense.

245
00:10:45,896 --> 00:10:47,055
We can't live together

246
00:10:47,056 --> 00:10:48,476
peacefully at all.

247
00:10:48,496 --> 00:10:49,956
Every day is suffering.

248
00:10:49,975 --> 00:10:50,734
Don't you want to know

249
00:10:50,735 --> 00:10:52,115
how he got injured?

250
00:10:52,136 --> 00:10:53,235
I'll tell you now.

251
00:10:53,416 --> 00:10:55,556
We live in separate rooms
since the beginning.

252
00:10:55,855 --> 00:10:56,974
He got very drunk that night

253
00:10:56,975 --> 00:10:57,895
and climbed on my bed,

254
00:10:57,896 --> 00:10:59,415
so I kicked him off.

255
00:10:59,416 --> 00:11:01,094
And that's how he got injured.

256
00:11:01,095 --> 00:11:02,295
Why do you have to say that?

257
00:11:02,296 --> 00:11:03,676
Why not?

258
00:11:05,136 --> 00:11:05,875
Well...

259
00:11:06,975 --> 00:11:08,734
You were the one

260
00:11:08,735 --> 00:11:10,375
who always wanted us

261
00:11:10,376 --> 00:11:11,574
to have a child of our own.

262
00:11:11,575 --> 00:11:12,295
A child?

263
00:11:12,296 --> 00:11:13,716
What are you talking about?

264
00:11:13,815 --> 00:11:15,275
You're daydreaming.

265
00:11:15,496 --> 00:11:16,775
I've warned you before.

266
00:11:16,776 --> 00:11:17,214
She'll never

267
00:11:17,215 --> 00:11:18,495
have a child with you

268
00:11:18,496 --> 00:11:20,796
because she had no plans
on building a family with you.

269
00:11:21,815 --> 00:11:23,135
- Where are you going?
- To work.

270
00:11:23,136 --> 00:11:24,035
Wait.

271
00:11:24,455 --> 00:11:25,476
Xiang Zhong.

272
00:11:26,136 --> 00:11:27,796
Guess what, I can tell.

273
00:11:28,095 --> 00:11:30,275
You've planned this for a long time.

274
00:11:30,496 --> 00:11:31,375
Now you want a divorce?

275
00:11:31,376 --> 00:11:32,716
It's not that easy.

276
00:11:32,776 --> 00:11:34,734
You kicked him off the bed

277
00:11:34,735 --> 00:11:35,854
and almost blinded him.

278
00:11:35,855 --> 00:11:38,535
It is a form of intentional assault.

279
00:11:38,536 --> 00:11:41,316
You'll be held criminally liable
for your actions, do you know that?

280
00:11:41,536 --> 00:11:42,995
Fine. Let me ask you this.

281
00:11:43,056 --> 00:11:44,734
Is it considered sexual assault

282
00:11:44,735 --> 00:11:46,415
if I was forced to live a married life

283
00:11:46,416 --> 00:11:47,676
despite my disapproval?

284
00:12:17,335 --> 00:12:19,596
Do you know
that your daughter wants a divorce?

285
00:12:20,335 --> 00:12:21,214
Why?

286
00:12:21,215 --> 00:12:21,655
How am I

287
00:12:21,656 --> 00:12:22,694
